29 transferred in accordance with IC 9-21-3.6. To the extent a person
30 to whom this subsection applies is liable for costs for a violation of
31 IC 9-21-12-1(a), the costs may be deducted only from the judgment
32 and may not cause the person to be liable for an amount greater
33 than the civil penalty under IC 9-21-3.6.
34 SECTION 19. IC 36-1-6-3 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
35 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3. (a) Certain
36 ordinances may be enforced by a municipal corporation without
37 proceeding in court through:
38 (1) an admission of violation before the violations clerk under
39 IC 33-36; or
40 (2) administrative enforcement under section 9 of this chapter.
41 (b) Except as provided in subsection (a), a proceeding to enforce an
42 ordinance must be brought in accordance with IC 34-28-5, section 4 of
2026 IN 1292—LS 6313/DI 137

26
1 this chapter, or both.
2 (c) An ordinance defining a moving traffic violation may not be
3 enforced under IC 33-36 and must be enforced in accordance with
4 IC 34-28-5.
5 (d) An ordinance adopted under IC 9-21-3.6 may be enforced
6 under IC 33-36 or IC 34-28-5.
